"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832661","Department for Education","false","2018-01-30","<p>We are consulting on the proposals in our green paper on Children and Young Peoples’ Mental Health published last month.</p><p> </p><p>Supported by over £300 million of funding it includes plans to train Mental Health Leads in schools, particularly in how to take a ‘whole school approach’ to promoting and supporting good mental health. Schools will also receive increased specialist support from new clinically-supervised Mental Health Support Teams.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2018-01-30T16:10:18.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832661/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832661/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832661/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-29","Pupils: Mental Health","1","House of Commons","What steps he is taking to improve the mental health of pupils in primary and secondary schools.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","903584"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832662","Department for Education","false","2018-01-29","<p>We have been strengthening the Special Educational Needs and Disabilities system through the biggest programme of reforms in a generation. We have legislated to improve the system and have invested £341 million since 2014 to help ensure the reforms make a real difference. We will continue to build on this, so that every child has the chance to fulfil their potential.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","903594 ; 903598 ; 903599","2018-01-29T16:30:28.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832662/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832662/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832662/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-29","Special Educational Needs","1","House of Commons","What steps his Department is taking to improve support for children with special educational needs and disabilities.","false","Biography information for Edward Argar","Charnwood","Edward Argar","903593"
