"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832664","Department for Education","false","2018-01-29","<p>The appointments to the Board were made through a fair and open competition, reflecting the Governance Code on Public appointments and the relevant legislation. The Board members have the broad range of skills and experience needed to lead the Office for Students to deliver better outcomes for students.</p><p> </p><p /><p />","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-01-29T16:35:35.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832664/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832664/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832664/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-29","Office for Students: Public Appointments","1","House of Commons","What assessment he has made of the effectiveness of the appointment process for the board of the Office for Students.","false","Biography information for Matt Western","Warwick and Leamington","Matt Western","903595"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832665","Department for Education","false","2018-01-29","<p>We have been strengthening the Special Educational Needs and Disabilities system through the biggest programme of reforms in a generation. We have legislated to improve the system and have invested £341 million since 2014 to help ensure the reforms make a real difference. We will continue to build on this, so that every child has the chance to fulfil their potential.</p>","Stratford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","903593 ; 903594 ; 903599","2018-01-29T16:30:28.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832665/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832665/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/832665/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-01-29","Special Educational Needs","1","House of Commons","What steps his Department is taking to improve support for children with special educational needs and disabilities.","false","Biography information for Gordon Henderson","Sittingbourne and Sheppey","Gordon Henderson","903598"
